1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:04,525
Deep in the Amazon, there is a man crowned with feathers.

2
00:00:04,575 --> 00:00:08,300
They say he saw all five of Brazil's world titles... before they happened.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:14,090
Tonight, he has a sixth vision.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,250
In episode four, we predicted a one-one storm in Texas.

5
00:00:20,300 --> 00:00:24,050
Tonight, the tournament stops pretending... because BRAZIL is here.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:29,805
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode five. Brazil versus Morocco.

7
00:00:29,855 --> 00:00:33,660
Group C. And the whole planet is watching.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,495
One hundred ninety-six million Brazilians. Thirty-seven million Moroccans. One ball.

9
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:45,040
And a secret the kings of football would rather forget.

10
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,460
Five stars. Fifty-eight. Sixty-two. Seventy. Ninety-four. Two thousand two.

11
00:00:50,510 --> 00:00:54,470
No nation has more.

12
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,023
But look closer at that last star... two thousand two.

13
00:00:59,073 --> 00:01:02,097
Brazil has not touched the trophy in twenty-four years.

14
00:01:02,147 --> 00:01:05,170
The longest wait in their history.

15
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:10,837
And Morocco?

16
00:01:10,887 --> 00:01:14,223
In twenty twenty-two they became the FIRST African and Arab nation ever to reach a World Cup semifinal.

17
00:01:14,273 --> 00:01:17,610
Spain — gone. Portugal — gone.

18
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:24,885
Now the secret. March, twenty twenty-three. Tangier. The last time these two met...

19
00:01:24,935 --> 00:01:30,320
Morocco WON. Two-one. The first Moroccan victory over Brazil in history.

20
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,310
And the man who created the first goal that night... is on the pitch again tonight.

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:43,150
So meet the kings. The yellow machine chasing the Hexa — the sixth star.

22
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:49,320
Vinicius Junior. Twenty-five. Two Champions League titles.

23
00:01:49,370 --> 00:01:54,190
His dribbling defies physics — his joy is a love letter to the beautiful game.

24
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:57,920
Neymar — thirty-four now, dropping deep, seeing passes nobody else can imagine.

25
00:01:57,970 --> 00:02:01,290
Raphinha stretches the world. And behind them all...

26
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:04,660
Alisson, the calmest man in football.

27
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,380
When Brazil plays, the world stops. That is the law.

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,570
But Morocco does not stop for anyone. Compact. Disciplined.

29
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:21,190
Fearless — and they have already beaten these kings once.

30
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,645
Achraf Hakimi — arguably the best right-back on Earth.

31
00:02:27,695 --> 00:02:31,840
Born in Madrid, heart in Rabat. His penalty eliminated Spain itself.

32
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,303
Hakim Ziyech, the wand of a left foot.

33
00:02:36,353 --> 00:02:39,657
Sofyan Amrabat, the engine of the semifinal run.

34
00:02:39,707 --> 00:02:43,010
And El Khannouss — the kid who unlocked Brazil in Tangier.

35
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,410
This is not an underdog. This is a trap.

36
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,620
And the duel inside the match: Vinicius against Hakimi.

37
00:02:52,670 --> 00:02:55,790
The fastest winger alive against the fastest defender alive. Lightning...

38
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:58,960
against lightning.

39
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:03,415
The Prophet's vision — built on five stars, one drought, and one night in Tangier.

40
00:03:03,465 --> 00:03:06,380
Watch.

41
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:14,365
Sixty-seventh minute. Morocco counter. Hakimi — SHOT! Alisson saves!

42
00:03:14,415 --> 00:03:20,280
The rebound — En-Nesyri header — CLEARED OFF THE LINE! Inches from silence.

43
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:27,130
The kings are shaking. The Lions can smell it. And the clock keeps breathing...

44
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:33,975
Seventy-eighth minute. Neymar. Thirty-five yards. Three defenders around him...

45
00:03:34,025 --> 00:03:37,500
and he sees what nobody sees.

46
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:43,905
A no-look pass that bends the laws of physics — VINI — cuts inside — GOAL! One-nil!

47
00:03:43,955 --> 00:03:48,360
A billion voices exhale at once!

48
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:54,313
Full time. The Prophet's vision: Brazil survive, one-nil.

49
00:03:54,363 --> 00:03:58,677
But hear this — Morocco walked toe-to-toe with the kings...

50
00:03:58,727 --> 00:04:03,040
and the Lions' roar echoes louder than the scoreline.

51
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:07,210
Do you agree with the vision? Comment HEXA if Brazil wins it all this summer.

52
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:10,970
Comment LIONS if Morocco tops Group C instead.

53
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:19,350
And the man with the feathers? Legend number five: The Feathered Prophet.

54
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:24,250
Five visions. Five stars. They say Pele's spirit speaks through him.

55
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,980
Tonight he saw the sixth begin. Collect him inside the game.

56
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,637
Which brings us to YOU.

57
00:04:35,687 --> 00:04:38,823
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

58
00:04:38,873 --> 00:04:42,010
scores for you.

59
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:49,600
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple. Your picks change everything.

60
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:54,120
Hit like — send this to the friend who thinks Brazil is unbeatable.

61
00:04:54,170 --> 00:04:58,090
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

